1
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:39,020
[A Love Never Lost]

2
00:01:40,539 --> 00:01:41,950
[Episode 22]

3
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:44,590
Commander Zhang,

4
00:01:45,509 --> 00:01:47,710
now that you're
the Southern Army's commander,

5
00:01:47,710 --> 00:01:49,509
you sure know how to impress us.

6
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:51,330
One question from you,

7
00:01:51,430 --> 00:01:52,640
and even our chief judge

8
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:54,400
is stumped.

9
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:58,550
Sir,

10
00:01:58,789 --> 00:02:00,640
the track gauge in Wuhan

11
00:02:00,890 --> 00:02:03,140
is 4.85 feet.

12
00:02:03,770 --> 00:02:04,770
Same

13
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,030
as in Beijing.

14
00:02:07,450 --> 00:02:08,780
I just got off the train,

15
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:11,120
and I sent someone to measure the tracks.

16
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,750
The gauge in Zhangde

17
00:02:14,030 --> 00:02:16,800
is also 4.85 feet.

18
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:21,280
This proves one thing:

19
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,360
corruption's the same everywhere!

20
00:02:29,630 --> 00:02:30,630
Commander Zhang,

21
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:33,090
our railway gauge standard

22
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,340
comes from Europe.

23
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:37,970
It was set by Europeans.

24
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:39,280
Is that so?

25
00:02:40,470 --> 00:02:41,360
Then

26
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:42,470
why did they set it

27
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:43,680
at 4.85?

28
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:45,560
Why not 4.86

29
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,280
or 3.86?

30
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:50,360
Why exactly 4.85?

31
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,680
Exactly.

32
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:52,860
Good question.

33
00:02:55,630 --> 00:02:57,470
The European railway gauge

34
00:02:58,150 --> 00:03:00,630
came from
the wheelbase of European carriages.

35
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:02,690
The wheelbase of European carriages

36
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:05,910
is exactly 4.85 feet.

37
00:03:07,030 --> 00:03:08,750
And why is the wheelbase

38
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:10,470
that wide?

39
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,930
You really know how to argue.

40
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:18,150
Because that's the width

41
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:20,280
of two horses side by side—

42
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,940
their rumps set the standard:

43
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:23,390
4.85 feet.

44
00:03:25,030 --> 00:03:26,090
So that's how it is.

45
00:03:29,630 --> 00:03:31,120
Kaizhi,

46
00:03:31,630 --> 00:03:33,840
you really are a man of knowledge!

47
00:03:34,910 --> 00:03:35,470
Cheers.

48
00:03:38,470 --> 00:03:39,680
Chief Judge,

49
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:42,030
your man is really something.

50
00:03:42,329 --> 00:03:43,650
Now I'm relieved.

51
00:03:44,470 --> 00:03:46,680
If he were any weaker,

52
00:03:47,030 --> 00:03:47,910
he really couldn't

53
00:03:47,910 --> 00:03:49,770
handle certain people out there.

54
00:03:53,110 --> 00:03:54,480
Look at that.

55
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:57,470
The drill hasn't even started yet,

56
00:03:57,470 --> 00:03:59,840
and someone's already
buttering up the brass!

57
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:02,960
If you're to suck up,
don't just do it to one person.

58
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:05,270
Make sure both men in power

59
00:04:05,290 --> 00:04:07,680
feel flattered.

60
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,190
Am I right?

61
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:12,120
That's right.

62
00:04:21,269 --> 00:04:22,040
Duan,

63
00:04:22,430 --> 00:04:23,680
why are you leaving?

64
00:04:24,190 --> 00:04:26,110
I was just kidding. Come on.

65
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:30,710
The Western food

66
00:04:31,110 --> 00:04:32,420
is awful.

67
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:33,790
Who came up with it?

68
00:04:34,830 --> 00:04:36,560
Come on, brothers,

69
00:04:37,159 --> 00:04:38,290
drink as you please.

70
00:04:38,350 --> 00:04:38,830
Cheers.

71
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,040
Cheers.

72
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:41,070
Cheers.

73
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:42,409
Let's drink.

74
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:53,920
Don't take it the wrong way, Chief Judge.

75
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:55,240
Before the drill,

76
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,680
I wouldn't dare offend you.

77
00:04:58,310 --> 00:04:59,370
It's totally fine.

78
00:04:59,430 --> 00:05:01,000
General Zhang, you have a sharp eye.

79
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,030
I should be learning from you.

80
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:13,390
Commander Zhang,

81
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:16,280
you must've come from the artillery corps.

82
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:17,500
How did you know?

83
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:18,800
Artillerymen

84
00:05:19,070 --> 00:05:20,680
are always obsessed with measurements,

85
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,360
and

86
00:05:21,510 --> 00:05:22,710
they always use feet.

87
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:26,120
Kaizhi,

88
00:05:26,510 --> 00:05:28,240
I have high hopes for you.

89
00:05:28,430 --> 00:05:30,000
Our border hero,

90
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:31,160
come.

91
00:05:39,290 --> 00:05:40,409
See?

92
00:05:41,770 --> 00:05:44,500
The two armies haven't even faced off yet,

93
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:47,790
and the tension
is already thick in the air.

94
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:50,070
That's why it's even more important

95
00:05:50,070 --> 00:05:51,360
for us judges

96
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,130
to stay fair and impartial.

97
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:57,630
If Manchu generals
want to lead Han soldiers,

98
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,040
they should study

99
00:06:00,060 --> 00:06:01,770
Han culture more.

100
00:06:02,630 --> 00:06:05,950
Han culture values flexibility,

101
00:06:06,390 --> 00:06:07,950
not rigid rules.

102
00:06:09,270 --> 00:06:10,240
My friend.

103
00:06:19,830 --> 00:06:20,510
The Commander-in-Chief

104
00:06:20,510 --> 00:06:21,840
has changed his stance.

105
00:06:24,730 --> 00:06:26,290
I told you long ago.

106
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:29,120
Don't take it too seriously.

107
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:31,070
It's all about mutual favors—

108
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:32,470
you help me, or I help you.

109
00:06:33,230 --> 00:06:33,760
Come on,

110
00:06:34,550 --> 00:06:35,680
don't look so upset.

111
00:06:35,990 --> 00:06:36,830
Come with me over there

112
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:37,920
and greet those

113
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:39,120
brigade commanders.

114
00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:40,190
Let's go.

115
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:47,470
[Imperial Bank of China]

116
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:48,360
Miss,

117
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,440
are these the correct amounts?

118
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:49,909
Yes.

119
00:06:49,940 --> 00:06:50,560
Shuhong.

120
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,050
Alright, wait a moment.

121
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:55,830
It's really you.

122
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:57,240
Yeah, it's me.

123
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:59,020
I could tell from afar.

124
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,040
What?

125
00:07:00,310 --> 00:07:01,710
You're back in Shanghai?

126
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,360
Yihua.

127
00:07:03,870 --> 00:07:06,520
The carriage is about to leave.
I've got business.

128
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:07,470
Coming, coming!

129
00:07:07,630 --> 00:07:09,180
You go ahead. We'll catch up later.

130
00:07:09,180 --> 00:07:11,110
Sure. Come visit when you're free.

131
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:13,760
You're still so beautiful.

132
00:07:15,550 --> 00:07:16,280
Who was that?

133
00:07:16,700 --> 00:07:17,960
Your third son's wife.

134
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,890
Still as pretty as ever.

135
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:26,840
Brother-in-law.

136
00:07:34,510 --> 00:07:35,570
Had another fight?

137
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:36,390
You bet.

138
00:07:36,870 --> 00:07:37,750
A big one.

139
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:40,570
Since you came back this time,

140
00:07:40,570 --> 00:07:42,430
you two have always been arguing.

141
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,930
What's really going on?

142
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,450
Your brother-in-law…

143
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:48,010
Forgive me for being blunt.

144
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:50,050
He's just not cut out to be a leader.

145
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:51,510
To be honest with you,

146
00:07:51,510 --> 00:07:52,270
I've already teamed up

147
00:07:52,270 --> 00:07:53,190
with comrades in Shanghai

148
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:54,120
to take him down.

149
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,190
In my opinion,

150
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:59,860
he's only good for writing his theories.

151
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,120
The most important thing right now

152
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,600
is the Zhejiang-Anhui uprising.

153
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,200
Success or failure doesn't matter.

154
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,860
We just have to make it happen.

155
00:08:07,510 --> 00:08:08,190
We need

156
00:08:08,190 --> 00:08:09,270
those donors to see exactly

157
00:08:09,270 --> 00:08:09,920
where

158
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,240
their money went,

159
00:08:11,470 --> 00:08:13,800
how we spent it,
and whether it was worth it.

160
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,510
Whether we succeed doesn't matter.

161
00:08:15,510 --> 00:08:16,510
But look at him—

162
00:08:17,070 --> 00:08:18,870
keeping saying we're not ready.

163
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:21,000
He's just being unreasonable!

164
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:29,680
Did the money for Qiu Jin and Xu Xilin

165
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,540
get delivered?

166
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:32,520
It's all been handed over.

167
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:35,320
Well,

168
00:08:35,870 --> 00:08:37,280
keep Zhangde's money separate.

169
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,679
We might need it anytime.

170
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:40,549
Didn't Wang Han take some money?

171
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,960
That was for operational expenses.

172
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,620
I'm talking about the pension

173
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:46,050
for Wang Han's family.

174
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:48,430
A pension for Wang Han's family?

175
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:49,510
Why so surprised?

176
00:08:49,850 --> 00:08:51,060
He's alive today,

177
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,260
but who knows about tomorrow?

178
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:59,020
You're really cold-blooded.

179
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:00,600
If one gives
one's life for the revolution,

180
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:01,600
it's worth it.

181
00:09:01,810 --> 00:09:03,020
But their families

182
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:04,240
still have to live on.

183
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:18,560
Attention!

184
00:09:20,790 --> 00:09:21,360
Salute!

185
00:09:46,930 --> 00:09:47,530
Giddy-up!

186
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:49,840
Giddy-up!

187
00:09:52,590 --> 00:09:53,120
Stop!

188
00:09:56,060 --> 00:09:57,120
What are you doing?

189
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:03,060
Enjoying yourself, Kaizhi?

190
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:04,300
This rain is perfect.

191
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:06,490
You're my superior.

192
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:08,670
I have to join you
in this romantic moment.

193
00:10:08,670 --> 00:10:10,260
But if I catch a cold when we arrive,

194
00:10:10,260 --> 00:10:11,520
I'll have to blame you.

195
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:13,700
You, come here!

196
00:10:20,910 --> 00:10:21,840
What's going on?

197
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:28,860
The assassin ran that way!

198
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,360
Stop! Stop!

199
00:10:38,330 --> 00:10:39,880
Stop! Don't run!

200
00:10:48,950 --> 00:10:49,970
The assassin is in the hotel.

201
00:10:49,970 --> 00:10:51,200
Surround the entire building.

202
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,000
Open the door!

203
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:56,030
Open the door!

204
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:57,670
Coming. Coming.

205
00:10:58,030 --> 00:11:01,240
Open up! Open up!

206
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,150
Fool!

207
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,400
Dying for you people
really isn't worth it!

208
00:11:09,290 --> 00:11:10,090
Out of the way!

209
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:11,790
Search the place!

210
00:11:11,790 --> 00:11:12,240
Yes.

211
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:13,290
You, go that way.

212
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:13,720
Yes.

213
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:18,480
Sir.

214
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:09,760
[Northern Army Camp]

215
00:12:23,790 --> 00:12:24,790
What is it, Chief Judge?

216
00:12:24,790 --> 00:12:26,120
The confrontation time has passed.

217
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,980
Why hasn't anything started yet?

218
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,480
Can't be helped.

219
00:12:30,030 --> 00:12:31,960
The Southern Army hasn't arrived.

220
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:37,790
Everyone, stand up!

221
00:12:41,790 --> 00:12:42,790
Salute!

222
00:12:45,910 --> 00:12:46,550
Renjun,

223
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:49,110
I heard that
some battalions in the Northern Army

224
00:12:49,110 --> 00:12:50,360
have canceled the military salute

225
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:51,760
and changed it to bowing.

226
00:12:51,980 --> 00:12:52,710
Is that true?

227
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,980
The Ninth Battalion
just got a new Manchu commander.

228
00:12:54,980 --> 00:12:56,420
He said the Commander-in-Chief, Feng Shan,

229
00:12:56,420 --> 00:12:57,850
approved the change.

230
00:12:59,620 --> 00:13:00,270
Really?

231
00:13:01,060 --> 00:13:02,600
The Commander-in-Chief approved it?

232
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:03,790
What can we do?

233
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,650
I can't control others,

234
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:07,030
but my men won't change.

235
00:13:07,030 --> 00:13:08,850
Whoever dares to change,
I'll kick their ass.

236
00:13:08,850 --> 00:13:10,090
An army is an army!

237
00:13:11,030 --> 00:13:12,090
Looks like Mr. Yuan

238
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:13,910
really picked the right man back then.

239
00:13:13,910 --> 00:13:14,720
Of course.

240
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:16,600
A man's gotta know gratitude—

241
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,120
always stay proper,

242
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:19,670
righteous, grounded,

243
00:13:19,670 --> 00:13:20,440
and clean.

244
00:13:30,380 --> 00:13:31,220
Qianli,

245
00:13:32,260 --> 00:13:33,660
why do Northern soldiers

246
00:13:34,150 --> 00:13:36,210
hang their shoes around their necks?

247
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:40,750
Chief Judge,

248
00:13:40,910 --> 00:13:42,510
you shouldn't ask me that.

249
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,240
You should ask the new quartermaster.

250
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,570
The new quartermaster?

251
00:13:45,790 --> 00:13:47,440
He was just transferred here
two weeks ago.

252
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:49,150
He's the Commander-in-Chief's
brother-in-law.

253
00:13:49,150 --> 00:13:50,350
You'd better ask him.

254
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:52,340
The joint drill is about to start,

255
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,910
and they're all barefoot?

256
00:13:53,910 --> 00:13:55,910
Tell them to put their shoes on. Now!

257
00:13:58,390 --> 00:13:59,080
Put them on!

258
00:13:59,270 --> 00:13:59,960
Quickly!

259
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:02,150
Quickly!

260
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:11,790
Tell me.

261
00:14:12,290 --> 00:14:13,490
What's going on here?

262
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:16,440
For this autumn military drill,

263
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,700
because of the parade,

264
00:14:18,150 --> 00:14:20,670
all officers and soldiers
are required to wear leather shoes.

265
00:14:20,670 --> 00:14:22,000
The shoes were all custom-ordered

266
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,790
by the new quartermaster in Tianjin.

267
00:14:23,790 --> 00:14:24,480
Who knows

268
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,910
how much money he pocketed from this?

269
00:14:25,910 --> 00:14:27,000
The shoes all came out

270
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:27,910
too small.

271
00:14:27,910 --> 00:14:29,030
In a whole company, only 11 or 12 men

272
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:30,150
can actually wear them.

273
00:14:30,150 --> 00:14:31,150
As for the rest...

274
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,130
Is the entire Northern Army

275
00:14:34,150 --> 00:14:35,210
in this situation?

276
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:35,670
Yes.

277
00:14:36,030 --> 00:14:36,550
All the shoes

278
00:14:36,550 --> 00:14:38,440
were ordered by that quartermaster.

279
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:40,550
The Commander-in-Chief's brother-in-law,

280
00:14:40,550 --> 00:14:41,480
what's his name?

281
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:43,480
Qide, with Qi meaning inspiration
and De meaning

282
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:44,150
virtue.

283
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:46,840
Inspiration and virtue?

284
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:49,640
More like lack of virtue!

285
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,870
If they don't fit,
we can just go barefoot.

286
00:15:06,090 --> 00:15:07,760
Without shoes, we can still defeat them,

287
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:08,330
can't we?

288
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:09,550
Yes!

289
00:15:10,550 --> 00:15:11,150
However,

290
00:15:11,630 --> 00:15:13,240
if we go barefoot in the parade,

291
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:15,240
our steps won't sound crisp and loud.

292
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:16,440
So just bear with it.

293
00:15:16,670 --> 00:15:19,120
No matter how small
the shoes are, put them on.

294
